<paragraph blockId="32.[136,1452,1982,2081]" pageId="32" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,634,1982,2009]" pageId="32" pageNumber="93">Proposed IUCN conservation status:</emphasis>
—Vulnerable [VU B1ac (ii, iii)]. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Vidal" authorityYear="1886" box="[1022,1251,1982,2008]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="32" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barandana">
<emphasis box="[1022,1251,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="93">Berberis barandana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost always found associated with cloud forest, a highly threatened ecosystem in the 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1097,2018,2044]" name="Philippines" pageId="32" pageNumber="93">Philippines</collectingCountry>
due to rapid deforestation. We hereby propose a provisional IUCN category of VU for the species (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[900,1038,2055,2081]" pageId="32" pageNumber="93" refId="ref24146" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN red list category and criteria. Version 3.1. Second Edition. Gland and Cambridge, 32 pp." type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
